results.name: Decimal expansion of Product_{p prime} (1 - 7/p^3).
comment: This is the probability that k, k+1, ... k+6 all are cubefree, or equivalently, the asymptotic density of A328016.
link: Leon Mirsky, Arithmetical pattern problems relating to divisibility by rth powers, Proceedings of the London Mathematical Society, Vol. s2-50, No. 1 (1949), pp. 497-508.
mathematica: $MaxExtraPrecision = 600; m = 600; c = LinearRecurrence[{0, 0, 7}, {0, 0, -7}, m]; RealDigits[(1/8) * Exp[3*NSum[Indexed[c, n]*(PrimeZetaP[n] - 1/2^n)/n, {n, 2, m}, NSumTerms -> m, WorkingPrecision -> m]], 10, 100][[1]]
results.author: _Amiram Eldar_, Oct 01 2019
